It is my experience that some of the behavioral and/or personality problems with PTSD and Vietnam Veterans is that it can be transgenerational, especially for children in young families. I know there are some things about me connected with PTSD that unfortunately influenced my girls as they were growing up for which they are now just comming to grips. Like baby ducks, &quot;baby&quot; humans can suffer from imprinting of sorts.<br><br>
Believe me, generational effects are very, very real.
